Envestnet, Inc. Key Developments

First Citizens Wealth Management Selects Envestnet for Integrated Intelligent Platform
Jul 20 17
First Citizens Wealth Management announced that it has implemented an integrated platform by Envestnet, providing a more unified experience for financial advisors and enhanced client service. Envestnet’s platform provides First Citizens financial advisors, across all Wealth Management business lines, comprehensive access to powerful technologies and services enabling them to deliver client investment strategy and offerings from multiple proprietary and third-party strategies. Envestnet platform capabilities encompass proposal generation risk profiling, account onboarding, portfolio management, administrative workflow, client reporting and billing, compliance, and business management oversight tools.


Envestnet, Inc. Presents at In|Vest 2017, Jul-11-2017 02:50 PM
Jul 8 17
Envestnet, Inc. Presents at In|Vest 2017, Jul-11-2017 02:50 PM. Venue: New York Marriott Marquis, 1535 Broadway, New York 10036, New York, United States. Speakers: William C. Crager, President.


Envestnet | Yodlee Unveils Personal Financial Wellness Solution Powered by Data Intelligence
Jun 12 17
Envestnet | Yodlee announced the launch of its Personal Financial Wellness Solution at the Digital Banking Summit. The Envestnet | Yodlee Personal Financial Wellness is a suite of applications and APIs that leverages enriched data and artificial intelligence to move beyond organizing historical financial data, helping financial institutions and fintech developers provide actionable, financial guidance to their customers across a spectrum of devices, user interfaces and platforms. The Envestnet | Yodlee Personal Financial Wellness enables financial institutions and fintech developers to provide actionable tools to help consumers identify their projected OK to Spend balance and easily Save for a Goal. By applying Envestnet Yodlee's advanced data intelligence to its enriched transaction data of over 15,000 data sources, financial service providers can derive actionable information from consumers' financial data in order to measure, guide and improve consumers' financial health.


