CONFERENCE ONArchitectingIntelligenceSM
OCTOBER 15, 2016VIVANTA BY TAJ  |  TRIVANDRUM







Envestnet's multi-portal platform is a unified network focused on enhancing the wealth management process.  We harmonize data across the breadth of our network to deliver thoughtful, actionable intelligence that can foster growth and deliver better client outcomes. Our portals are complete solutions that can be accessed on the go and span the key elements of the advisory process.




















ABOUT THE CONFERENCE

This year, in the second edition of the Conference on Architecting Intelligence,we bring together Futurists, Bankers, Financial Advisors and Software Architects to exchange perspectives, share knowledge, challenge assumptions and empower businesses.
Great Solutions happen at the intersection of disciplines.










                "I believe that there is no industry on Earth more conducive for leveraging digital technology than our own wealth management business." 


   - Jud Bergman at the Envestnet Advisor Summit,2016, Chicago.




Machines learn.
In fact, they can train themselves.
Learning from each exposure, cognitive algorithms rapidly mature, re-adjusting assumptions and refining models because at their core, lies Intelligence.
Augment Human Will and Rationality with  Machine Learning (which enable humans make final selections from a range of intelligent choices) – and you have the blueprint of the future. 
Machine Learning and subsequently Cognitive Computing would  redefine and impact every imaginable domain and discipline.
Wealth Management undoubtedly, would be one of the most influenced, disrupted and augmented spaces, for entirely rational reasons: huge volumes of data, variety of variables, and the uncertain dynamics between influential factors ranging from probability to psychology, would demand augmented intelligence.
 
Concept Paper  Architecting Intelligence in Wealth Management





MEET OUR SPEAKERS
















































Gerd Leonhard
Futurist, Humanist, CEO
The Futures Agency

Gerd Leonhard is a widely-known and top-rated Futurist. Gerd focuses on near-future, ‘nowist’ observations and actionable foresight in the sectors of humanity, society, business and commerce, media, technology and communications. Gerd is an influential author, a sought-after executive ‘future trainer’ and a trusted strategic advisor. Gerd is also the host of the web-TV series ‘The Future Show’ and CEO of The Futures Agency, a global network of over 30 leading futurists. 
Gerd is considered a leading voice on a wide range of topics including digital transformation and the discovery of digitally-native business models. In 2006, The Wall Street Journal called Gerd ‘one of the leading Media Futurists in the World’. In 2015, Wired Magazine listed Gerd as one of the top 100 influencers in Europe.
Catch Gerd as he speaks about Architecting Intelligence in the second edition of the Conference.










Lincoln Ross
Executive Vice President
Envestnet, Inc

Ross is responsible for Strategy and Marketing.
Prior to joining Envestnet, Ross was President and CEO of FundQuest, Inc. Ross joined FundQuest in 1998 and worked with the founding team to grow and evolve the company through its merger with BNP Paribas in 2005 and subsequent sale to Envestnet in 2011.
Ross received his B.A. from the University of New Hampshire and M.S. from Boston University.
Catch Ross as he speaks about Technology Transformation in Wealth Management at the Conference on Architecting Intelligence.










Prof. Dr. U. Dinesh Kumar
Professor
Indian Institute of Management, Bangalore

Dr. U. Dinesh Kumar, Professor, Quantitative Methods & Information Systems, Indian Institute of Management, Bangalore (IIMB), has been recognized as one of the Top 10 Most Prominent Analytic Academicians in India for his research in big data analyses (Analytics India Magazine).
As course director- Business Analytics and Intelligence Executive Education Program of IIMB, Prof. Dinesh Kumar has trained over 1000 professionals in the field of analytics. He has published 11 case studies on the use of predictive and prescriptive analytics by Indian companies at the Harvard Business Publishing and is president of the Analytics Society of India (ASI).
Catch Prof. Dinesh as he speaks about Analytics: Data Modeling, Cleansing, and Enriching at the Conference on Architecting Intelligence.










Arjun Singh
Managing Director, Asia 
Envestnet Yodlee

Arjun Singh heads up Envestnet Yodlee’s growing India Operations. A leading data aggregation and data analytics platform, Envestnet Yodlee powers dynamic, cloud-based innovation for digital financial services. Arjun oversees Yodlee’s large development center in Bangalore and spearheads international growth in the region.
With more than 25 years of experience running and growing businesses, Arjun has played senior roles at Aon Hewitt in Asia, WNS in India and the UK, ABN AMRO Bank in Amsterdam, GE Capital Information Services, and ANZ Grindlays Bank in Delhi and Melbourne.
Catch Arjun as he moderates a panel discussion on Financial Services in APAC at the Conference on Architecting Intelligence.










Dr. Parag Kulkarni
Founder CEO and Chief Scientist
EKLaT Research & iknowlation Research Labs Pvt. Ltd.

A sought after Innovation Strategist and Machine Learning expert, Dr. Parag Kulkarni is a leading authority in business, knowledge and innovation strategies. An expert in Text and Data Analytics with more than two decades of Industry, Research and Management experience, Dr. Parag is consultant in areas of knowledge management, machine learning, value innovation, business and IT strategy, and data mining.
An alumnus of IIT Karagpur and IIM Kolkata, Dr. Parag has been conferred the DSc – Higher Doctorate by the UGSM Monarch Business School – Swiss University, for his contributions and research in Knowledge Innovation and Machine Learning. He has worked extensively on strategy formulation and implementation, developed and delivered products based on research in the areas of AI and Machine learning.
Catch Dr. Parag as he speaks about Machine Learning: Models and Algorithms at the Conference on Architecting Intelligence










Blake Wood
Senior Vice President, Director of Program Innovation 
Envestnet, Inc

Blake Wood leads Program Innovation at Envestnet, supporting ENV business development efforts, strategic client engagements as well as product release communications.
The Program Innovation Group represents the investor, advisor and enterprise voice into Envestnet and is the voice of Envestnet product and development groups back to Envestnet partners. The group works closely with integration partners and strategic stakeholders to create and define Envestnet’s vision for moving forward.
Blake’s specialties’ include Customer platform integrations/migrations, Separately Managed Accounts, Customer Service, Project Management and Implementations, Education and Training, Web Demonstrations, Rebalancing Tools.










Ravi Shankar
Co Founder and CEO
Active Intelligence Pte

Prior to being an entrepreneur, he worked for nearly 20 years across HDFC Bank, ABN AMRO Bank and YES BANK in various senior executive roles. In his banking career he pioneered India into Electronic Real Time Payments, Mobile Payments, Chip Cards, Wallets, Apps, well before they became buzzwords of today. Over the last 5 years he has partnered great teams and entrepreneurs across countries building next generation Fintech and Technology companies.Ravishankar has been closely associated with Yodlee in Asia. He partnered Yodlee as it’s first banking customer in 2008 through YESBANK. 










Pramod Singh
Chief Analytics Officer and Vice President of Data Sciences and Analytics
Envestnet | Yodlee

Pramod Singh is Chief Analytics Officer and Vice President of Data Sciences and Analytics at  Envestnet | Yodlee based out of Bangalore. He leads 50+ member team comprising of  Data Scientists, Analytics Engineers and Business Analysts. He is responsible for delivering analytics solutions for the enterprise.  Before joining  Envestnet|Yodlee Pramod Singh was Director of Digital and Big Data Analytics at Hewlett Packard. He has more than 20 years of leadership experience in leading analytics teams and in design and implementation of analytics solutions. Pramod was with the HP since 2000 in different roles. For almost 15  years at HP, Pramod has lead advanced analytics teams in areas of customer knowledge management, e- business , global business intelligence in IT  and digital and big data analytics.. Before joining HP, Pramod worked at Wal-Mart’s Information systems. Here, he designed and developed advanced assortment planning system, a technology that  revolutionized the store assortment practices for Wal-Mart. Pramod has PhD and Masters in Mathematics from University of Arkansas and an MBA in Marketing. Pramod is author of several published papers and patent and regular speaker at international conferences. 










Prashant Paliwal
Sr. Director, Ecosystem Development & Innovation – APAC
Envestnet|Yodlee

Head of Ecosystem Development & Innovation, Prashant believes in customer driven innovation and is adept at analyzing data.












